006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.constraint;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IAssemblyDefinition;
009import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.constraint.impl.AbstractDefinitionTargetedConstraints;
010
011import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
012
013/**
014 * A set of constraints targeting a {@link IAssemblyDefinition} based on a
015 * target Metapath expression.
016 *
017 * @see #getTargetExpression()
018 */
019public class AssemblyTargetedConstraints
020    extends AbstractDefinitionTargetedConstraints<IAssemblyDefinition, IModelConstrained>
021    implements IFeatureModelConstrained {
022
023  /**
024   * Construct a new set of targeted constraints.
025   *
026   * @param target
027   *          the Metapath expression that can be used to find matching targets
028   * @param constraints
029   *          the constraints to apply to matching targets
030   */
031  public AssemblyTargetedConstraints(
032      @NonNull String target,
033      @NonNull IModelConstrained constraints) {
034    super(target, constraints);
035  }
036
037  @Override
038  public void target(@NonNull IAssemblyDefinition definition) {
039    applyTo(definition);
040  }
041
042  @Override
043  protected void applyTo(@NonNull IAssemblyDefinition definition) {
044    super.applyTo(definition);
045    getIndexConstraints().forEach(definition::addConstraint);
046    getUniqueConstraints().forEach(definition::addConstraint);
047    getHasCardinalityConstraints().forEach(definition::addConstraint);
048  }
049}
